image.altText: Tate McDermott of Australia receives medical attention during 2023 Rugby World Cup opener.

items.synopsis: Australia vice-captain Tate McDermott is forced from the field following a head knock, as the Wallabies add another try to their tally in the second half. Follow all the action in our live blog.

title.children: Wallabies lose McDermott but still on top of Georgia in Rugby World Cup opener

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Ben Donaldson scored the try, but it was Taniela Tupou who made it with a one-handed offload! Georgia had a fantastic break from Davit Niniashvili. He was tackled by Nic White, but tried an outrageous flick pass that flew straight to Tupou. He raced forward towards the line, offloaded and Donaldson did the rest. Good finish and so is the kick. The Wallabies lead 28-8.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: 56' Try Wallabies!

children.content: Ben Donaldson scored the try, but it was Taniela Tupou who made it with a one-handed offload!
Georgia had a fantastic break from Davit Niniashvili.
He was tackled by Nic White, but tried an outrageous flick pass that flew straight to Tupou.
He raced forward towards the line, offloaded and Donaldson did the rest.
Good finish and so is the kick.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Luka Matkava with a gorgeous pass over the top to Luka Ivanishvili on the left! He smashes over in the corner and the Georgians are rewarded for their bold line out kick for the penalty.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: 47' Georgia score!

children.content: Luka Matkava with a gorgeous pass over the top to Luka Ivanishvili on the left!
He smashes over in the corner and the Georgians are rewarded for their bold line out kick for the penalty.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Good start for the Wallabies there. They came out the blocks early and Mark Nawaqanitawase was particularly good in those opening exchanges. Georgia has been pretty rusty to be honest and do not look the standard that they have been. The only blemish on that half was the injury to Tate McDermott, who might have to miss a game or two after that nasty headknock.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Half time: Wallabies lead 21-3

children.content: Good start for the Wallabies there.
They came out the blocks early and Mark Nawaqanitawase was particularly good in those opening exchanges.
Georgia has been pretty rusty to be honest and do not look the standard that they have been.
The only blemish on that half was the injury to Tate McDermott, who might have to miss a game or two after that nasty headknock.
